\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 2. Tools & Systems Chosen\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 GitHub Actions\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 GitHub Actions is the CI/CD tool for this application. It is an automated workflow tool provided by GitHub that performs the actions defined in YAML files in cloud-based virtual machines (called "runners") whenever specific events happen.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 What it does in this project:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Continuous Integration (CI):
\f1\b0  With every push, GitHub Actions pulls the code and performs actions like installing the dependencies, running tests using pytest and Jest, building Docker image and checking if there are any errors in the process. Any failure in this pipeline will ensure that the pull request cannot go through until the error is fixed.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Continuous Deployment (CD):
\f1\b0  If CI/CD pipeline runs successfully in the master branch, GitHub Action automatically creates a production Docker image that is tagged by commit SHAs for future use in versioning, pushed to Amazon ECR, and a new App Runner deployment is kicked off. GitHub Action also builds the React frontend application and uploads it to S3.\
\ls2\ilvl0
\f0\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Scheduled monitoring:
\f1\b0  Every six hours a cron job will fire off to monitor the live backend and frontend, writing structured output logs as an artifact file available for download.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Amazon ECR (Elastic Container Registry)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Amazon ECR is the Amazon-managed private registry for hosting Docker images. The CI/CD workflow will create a FastAPI backend Docker image and push it to Amazon ECR. App Runner pulls this image to deploy the web app.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 AWS App Runner\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 App Runner is a fully managed AWS service that runs containerised web applications without requiring server or cluster management. It pulls images from ECR, handles scaling, and exposes an HTTPS endpoint automatically.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Amazon S3 + CloudFront\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The React frontend is a static build (HTML, CSS, JS files) that is synced to an S3 bucket. CloudFront distributes these files from edge locations globally, providing HTTPS and low-latency delivery.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Amazon RDS (PostgreSQL)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Backend persistently stores user accounts and resumes using a managed PostgreSQL database on RDS. DATABASE_URL gets stored in AWS Secret Manager and injected into App Runner as an environment variable during execution, thus never committed to the repository.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 AWS Secrets Manager\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Securely store sensitive credentials such as OpenAI API key and database URL. App Runner retrieves secrets directly from Secrets Manager during execution, ensuring that secrets never appear in source code or Docker images.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 GitHub Encrypted Secrets\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 All required AWS credentials (AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY) and other necessary parameters are defined as secrets in the GitHub repository. These secrets get injected into the running workflow as environment variables by the runner.\cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

