\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Triggers\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 on:\
  push:\
    branches: ['**']        # Every branch push - instant feedback\
  pull_request:\
    branches: [main]\
    paths:                  # Only when relevant files change (complex trigger)\
      - '**.py'\
      - '**.js'\
      - 'requirements.txt'\
      - 'Dockerfile'\
      - '.github/**'\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 The paths filter makes this a complex trigger, as GitHub checks if the file changed matches the globs specified before firing the job. Documentation-only commits (e.g. changing README.md) will not waste CI minutes on a useless run.\
