\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The Docker image is built with --platform linux/amd64 (needed because App Runner uses x86-64, while developers can run Apple Silicon Macs). Starts a Docker container locally and then checks if /health endpoint replies with HTTP 200 code. Finally stops the container.\
This validates that the Dockerfile is correct, main.py works and all imports were done correctly, catching Docker-specific failures that tests alone would miss.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

