\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 6. CD Workflow - Deep Dive\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 File: 
\f2\fs26 .github/workflows/cd.yml
\f1\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Complex Trigger 1 - Dependent workflow\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0 on:\
  workflow_run:\
    workflows: ['CI - Test & Validate']\
    branches: [main]\
    types: [completed]\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 The workflow_run event triggers when a specific workflow run ends. In turn, the gate job examines github.event.workflow_run.conclusion to ensure it equals 'success'. As such, it forms a dependency chain in which a code break on main prevents automatic deployment.
\f0\b\fs28 Complex Trigger 2 - Manual dispatch with conditions\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs26 \cf0   workflow_dispatch:\
    inputs:\
      skip_frontend:\
        type: boolean\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs24 \cf0 Conditional dispatching through manual dispatching: skipping frontend by setting skip_frontend to true will deploy only the backend services (if only Python scripts have been modified). This is a complicated trigger due to its dependency on the input parameters.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Job: 
\f3\fs30\fsmilli15210 deploy-backend
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\fs24 \cf0 Step-by-step:
\f1\b0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
configure-aws-credentials
\f1\b0\fs24  - injects 
\f2\fs26 AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID
\f1\fs24  and 
\f2\fs26 AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY
\f1\fs24  from GitHub Secrets as environment variables for all subsequent AWS CLI calls.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
amazon-ecr-login
\f1\b0\fs24  - authenticates the Docker daemon to the ECR registry using a short-lived token (valid 12 hours). No long-lived Docker credentials are stored anywhere.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
docker build
\f1\b0\fs24  - builds the image with two tags:\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-1440\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f4 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
:$\{\{ github.sha \}\}
\f1\fs24  - an 
\f0\b immutable revision tag
\f1\b0  tied to a specific commit. This tag never changes, so any past deployment can be reproduced exactly.\
\ls7\ilvl1
\f2\fs26 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	
\f4 \uc0\u9702 
\f2 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
:latest
\f1\fs24  - a mutable convenience tag that always points to the most recent push.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
docker push
\f1\b0\fs24  - pushes both tags. The SHA tag permanently records this deployment revision in ECR's image history, satisfying the "preserve deployment revisions" requirement.\
\ls7\ilvl0
\f3\b\fs26 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
aws apprunner start-deployment
\f1\b0\fs24  - triggers App Runner to pull the new 
\f2\fs26 :latest
\f1\fs24  image and create a new revision. App Runner's revision system also independently tracks every deployment.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls7\ilvl0
\f0\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	6	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Polling loop
\f1\b0  - checks 
\f2\fs26 describe-service
\f1\fs24  every 30 seconds until the status is 
\f2\fs26 RUNNING
\f1\fs24 . This makes the pipeline synchronous: downstream jobs (frontend deploy) only start after the backend is confirmed healthy.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Job: 
\f3\fs30\fsmilli15210 deploy-frontend
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Needs uses: deploy-backend, which guarantees the backend is running before the frontend update. This is because the React build comes out through the REACT_APP_API_URL, which gets inputted through the use of GitHub Secrets.\
S3 sync uses 
\f0\b separate cache headers
\f1\b0  for different file types:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Hashed Assets (main.abc123.js) max-age=31536000 (1 year) \'96 Safe as the hash is always unique for each asset.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\f2\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
 index.html and JSON no-cache \'96 Should always be fresh so the browser gets the latest entry point.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0
\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls8\ilvl0\cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
{\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}Job: 
\f3\fs30\fsmilli15210 record-deployment
\f0\fs28 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Creates a deployment.json artifact that contains commit SHA, run ID, actor, time stamp, and the status of the components. The artifact is kept for one year and can be used to rollback the pipeline execution or audit without rerunning the pipeline.\cf4 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 7. Health Check Workflow - Deep Dive\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

