\fs28 \cf0 GitHub Actions runner\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The worker gets a newly created Ubuntu 22.04 VM from GitHub. The worker already comes with Docker, Python, Node.js, AWS CLI, and curl installed. The VM will get deleted once the job finishes - there is no persistence between job executions (that\'92s why caching pip/npm packages is necessary). \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b \cf0 Alternative:
\f1\b0  Self-hosted runners -GitHub lets you connect your own computers to use as workers. This helps in cases when access to internal networks/hardware is needed for jobs. In our case, hosted workers work just fine.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Amazon ECR\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 In ECR, each Docker image is stored using a chain of layers that are immutable in nature. Every Docker image is represented by a unique hash digest in SHA-256 format and may be further assigned additional human-friendly labels such as :latest or :abc1234. Every Docker image uploaded to Amazon ECR is saved forever.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

