\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 Amazon RDS (PostgreSQL)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 RDS comes up with a managed PostgreSQL database with automatic backups, minor version upgrades, and multi-AZ failovers. There are no credentials stored within the application, as the app runner retrieves the connection string from secrets manager.\
In CI, database testing is done using a temporary SQLite in-memory database (using DATABASE_URL=sqlite:///./test_temp.db), to prevent:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls11\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Maintaining access to a database through the network \
\ls11\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Creating/deleting data used for testing on the production system\
\ls11\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
Dependence on Postgres in CI\
\ls11\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 AWS Secrets Manager\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The API key for the OpenAI API, as well as the DATABASE_URL for the PostgreSQL database, is stored in the Secrets Manager. This is critical, because these two variables will not be included in any form in the Docker image, repository, or App Runner environment variable plaintext.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

